      • query

        public Iterator<E> query(E o,
                         int ID)
                  throws IllegalArgumentException
        Queries the list by performing a sequential scan. Returns all elements that match with the given element o according to the user-defined binary query-predicate. The query-predicates are set via the #initialize(int, xxl.core.predicates.Predicate[]) method, which is typically called inside the constructor of a SweepArea.
        Note: The returned iterator should not be used to remove any elements from this implementor!
        Specified by:
        query in interface SweepAreaImplementor<E>
        Specified by:
        query in class AbstractSAImplementor<E>
        Parameters:
        o - The query object.
        ID - An ID determining from which input this method is triggered.
        Returns:
        An iterator delivering all matching elements.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Throws an IllegalArgumentException if something goes wrong with the query operation due to the passed argument.
        See Also:
        AbstractSAImplementor.filter(Iterator, Object, int)

      • query

        public Iterator<E> query(E[] os,
                         int[] IDs,
                         int valid)
                  throws IllegalArgumentException
        Description copied from class: AbstractSAImplementor
        The default implementation is restricted to the probing with single elements by calling the method AbstractSAImplementor.query(Object, int) on os[0] and IDs[0].
        Specified by:
        query in interface SweepAreaImplementor<E>
        Overrides:
        query in class AbstractSAImplementor<E>
        Parameters:
        os - The query objects. These objects are typically probed against the elements contained in this implementor.
        IDs - IDs determining from which input the query objects come from.
        valid - Determines how many entries at the beginning of os and IDs are valid and therefore taken into account.
        Returns:
        All matching elements of this SweepArea are returned as an iterator.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If valid is != 1.
